        "post_id": "2aab643b-d095-4c00-8b42-4f35379fb002",
        "user_id": 204864402,
        "body": "APPENDIX:\nI want to add something very important here.\nThis is the pre-projected dealer flow only, that is predestined, will happen no matter what, you can expect that and it takes a significant percentage (more than 70%) of the daily volume.\nAnybody who has basic knowledge about the greeks can describe what I described from this chart.\nHowever things are changing intraday too (especially if CBOE actually launches its 0.25DTE options, imagine how much gamma it will have), and these flows can shift if some big transaction hits. \nSo it is only one part of the puzzle. A very big part if not the biggest, but only one.  \n\nIn order to frontrun the market, you have to watch how the momentum evolved recently, how the pricings, the positionings shifted at certain events, at certain levels, in order to be able to see the story that the market wants to tell you. Just like I did on Sunday with the PS. \nIt wasn't the put spread itself, and the hedging flow derived from that, what made me bullish. It was the timing and the spot lvl of that PS with its dealer flow effect that made me bullish. \nDealer flow is an algorhytmic process. It is reflexive. It reacts to the customer flows. Market is stochastic. And big players can manipulate price actions through transactions into their favor. Manipulation is not always there. Herd also can have reflexive effects on it. The key is to see the flow of this ALL, in order to be able to frontrun the market.",
        "status": "published",
